===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|之|又|t1=to go|t2=hand|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|alt1=𡳿}} – to grasp, to hold. Phonetic 𡳿 ([[之]]), which represents a footprint pointing up, became {{zh-l|*土}} or {{zh-l|*士}} in the [[clerical script]] from the late Western Han to the Eastern Han, and semantic {{zh-l|*又}} became {{zh-l|*寸}} in Small Seal Script. The derivative {{och-l|持}} refers to the original word.

The character was often used in the place of a more specialized form. For example, in the {{w|Chu Silk Manuscript}} (see table above) it clearly stood for {{och-l|時|gloss=season}}.

